('Iâ€™ve created a new tool that might be helpful for future Core debugging purposes.  The name of this tool is called chronoParse.py (Located at /home/gtsman/managed-scripts/Testing).\r\n\r\nWhen debugging a specific Core application, many times you have to look at several applicationâ€™s logs as the components are interrelated.  This can get tedious as you have to compare side by side the timestamps/messages to pinpoint where something may have gone wrong.  This tool will help facilitate that process.\r\n\r\nWhat it does â€“ Compiles a series of desired messages (according to your filters) from multiple Core log files and prints them in chronological order into one log file.\r\nâ€¢	This script will take a series of arguments/Filters:\r\no	Log file name(s)/Host(s)\r\nï‚§	--log=PostProcessor.log,tc-pat204 --log=MatchingEngine.log,tc-pat202\r\no	Process name(s)\r\nï‚§	--proc=Pope-11_038 --proc=Matcher-11_038\r\no	Message Type(s)\r\nï‚§	--msg=default.INFO --msg=default.ERROR --msg=messaging.INFO\r\no	Environment Number\r\nï‚§	--env=038\r\no	Start Time â€“ This is the earliest moment in time in which messages you are looking for occurred\r\nï‚§	Y-M-DTH:M:S.MICROSEC\r\nï‚§	--start=2013-11-19T15:43:12.253757\r\no	End Time â€“ This is the latest moment in time in which messages you are looking for occurred\r\nï‚§	Y-M-DTH:M:S.MICROSEC\r\nï‚§	--end2013-11-19T17:43:12.253757\r\no	Output â€“ This is the name of the output file.  All messages that pass your filters will be printed to this log.  The log will have a timestamp according to when it was created.  This log will be stored inside your home directory at /home/USER/ChronoLogs\r\nï‚§	--out=ME_PP\r\nï‚§	Example output: ME_PP_2013-11-15_18-03-04.log\r\nâ€¢	Example usage:\r\no	./chronoParse.py --log=PostProcessor.log,tc-pat204 --proc=Pope-11_038 --log=MatchingEngine.log,tc-pat202 --proc=Matcher-11_038  --msg=default.ERROR --msg=messaging.INFO --start=2013-11-21T16:32:41.850144 --end=2013-11-21T16:32:42.141386 --env=038 --out=PP_ME_Test\r\nï‚§	This will look at both the Pope and ME logs on tc-pat204/tc-pat202 respectively (in environment 038) and search for all â€˜default.ERRORâ€™ and â€˜messaging.INFOâ€™ messages that occurred between â€˜2013-11-21T16:32:41.850144â€™ and â€˜2013-11-21T16:32:42.141386â€™.  All these messages will then be output to: /home/wassjas/ChronoLogs/PP_ME_Test_2013-11-22_16-18-50.log (Iâ€™ve copied this file to /home/gtsman/managed-scripts/Testing)\r\nï‚§	STDOUT\r\nParsing the following logs: [\\''PostProcessor.log,tc-pat204\\'', \\''MatchingEngine.log,tc-pat202\\'']\r\nSearching for the following processes: [\\''Pope-11_038\\'', \\''Matcher-11_038\\'']\r\nSearching for the following messages types: [\\''default.ERROR\\'', \\''messaging.INFO\\'']\r\nSearching between \\''2013-11-21T16:32:41.850144\\'' and \\''2013-11-21T16:32:42.141386\\''\r\nWriting to /home/wassjas/ChronoLogs/PP_ME_Test_2013-11-22_16-18-50.log...\r\n', '2013-11-26 15:01:12', 3),
