('RTP:\r\n\r\nWhat\\''s an easy to know that RTP is doing what it\\''s supposed to be doing?\r\n\r\nThe easiest way to check is to login to the market_place_oat DB and execute the following query if you have sent orders in the environment:\r\n\r\nSELECT * FROM order WHERE MRKT_DATE = \\''YYYY-MM-DD\\''\r\n\r\nYou can get details of the market_place_oat DB from the PluginManager config file\r\n', '2013-12-24 09:22:38', 27),
('Pope crash/won\\''t start-up --\r\nOne of the reason is in obsdb, table orderbook, and orderclearingrelation are in sync.\r\nOrderbook table contains all the order. For each of these order, the unique identifier is ExchangeOrderID and ProductID combination. (On different products, same exchange order ID can be used)\r\nIn orderclearingrelation table, it has additional information (one record for each CI leg for each order in the orderbook table) on the orders from orderbook table. It links back to orderbook table by ExchangeOrderID and ProductID combo. There can be multiple rows for each ExchOrdID and ProdID combo.\r\nSo if one of the combo exists in orderclearingrelation table but not in Orderbook table (and I assume vice versa), pope will crash on start-up. This has happened in production, due to cleanOrderbook\\''s faulty logic that deleted only entries from orderbook table.\r\nKeep in mind, even if they are not in sync, this bug might not trigger due to the way core checks the database. Pope looks at the orderbook table, and would determine the range of orders to check (from the smallest to largest in terms of ID), and then it verifies in ocr table that all orders within that range exists. So if the discrepancy occurs within that range, pope crashes. But if the discrepancy exists outside the range, like beyond the end of that range, then bug will not trigger.\r\n\r\nTo check for discrepancy using sql query --\r\nSELECT ocr.exchangeorderid,ocr.productid,ocr.position\r\nFROM obsdb21.orderclearingrelation ocr,\r\n     (SELECT ocr1.exchangeorderid,ocr1.productid\r\n      FROM obsdb21.orderclearingrelation ocr1\r\n           LEFT OUTER JOIN obsdb21.orderbook ob\r\n           ON ocr1.exchangeorderid = ob.exchangeorderid AND ocr1.productid = ob.productid\r\n      WHERE ob.productid IS NULL\r\n      GROUP BY ocr1.exchangeorderid,ocr1.productid) AS invalid_ocr\r\nWHERE ocr.exchangeorderid = invalid_ocr.exchangeorderid AND ocr.productid = invalid_ocr.productid\r\n\r\nTo manually sync the tables by deleting anything in ocr that\\''s not in orderbook table --\r\nDELETE ocr \r\nFROM obsdb21.orderclearingrelation ocr,\r\n     (SELECT ocr1.exchangeorderid,ocr1.productid\r\n      FROM obsdb21.orderclearingrelation ocr1\r\n           LEFT OUTER JOIN obsdb21.orderbook ob\r\n           ON ocr1.exchangeorderid = ob.exchangeorderid AND ocr1.productid = ob.productid\r\n      WHERE ob.productid IS NULL\r\n      GROUP BY ocr1.exchangeorderid,ocr1.productid) AS invalid_ocr\r\nWHERE ocr.exchangeorderid = invalid_ocr.exchangeorderid AND ocr.productid = invalid_ocr.productid\r\n', '2013-12-26 16:11:51', 28),
