('Requirements for using TIBCO API in Python:\r\n\r\n1. You need to install the PythonNet Python Module. This will allow you to use the C# DLLs from TIBCO or ISE Apps. Install the correct version for your python installation:\r\n    J:\\\\ASG\\\\RobotFramework\\\\Installation_Files\\\\pythonnet-2.0dev.win-amd64-py2.6.exe\r\n\r\n2. You need access to the TIBCO.EMS dll file. You can find this in the installation directory for an ISE App that uses TIBCO, such as tc-oat07a: D:\\\\ise\\\\iors_bsi_ora_01\\\\TIBCO.EMS.dll. Copy the DLL files to your Python installation\\''s DLL directory: C:\\\\Python26\\\\DLLs.\r\n\r\n3. Here\\''s some sample code:\r\n\r\nimport clr\r\nclr.AddReference(\\''TIBCO.EMS\\'')\r\nimport TIBCO.EMS\r\n\r\nconnection_factory = TIBCO.EMS.ConnectionFactory(\\"tcp://51.3.62.218:7222\\")\r\nconnection = connection_factory.CreateConnection(\\"\\", \\"\\")\r\nconnection.Start()\r\nsession = connection.CreateSession(False, TIBCO.EMS.Session.AUTO_ACKNOWLEDGE)\r\n\r\nsend_destination = session.CreateTopic(\\"temp_test_topic\\")\r\nproducer = session.CreateProducer(send_destination)\r\n\r\nreceive_destination = session.CreateTopic(\\"temp_test_topic\\")\r\nreceiver = session.CreateConsumer(receive_destination)\r\n\r\ntibco_message = session.CreateTextMessage(\\"This is my text message.\\")\r\ntibco_message.ReplyTo = receive_destination\r\nproducer.Send(tibco_message)\r\n\r\nmsg = receiver.Receive(10)\r\nif msg:\r\n    print msg\r\nelse:\r\n    print \\"No message\\"', '2014-01-10 15:02:27', 47),
