('Production GTC Checkout --\r\nGTCâ€™s will be tracked and monitored via email alerts and through the AOCC website. We will build upon the existing page (http://ic-aoc01/aoccbeta/coredata/gtcs) by adding additional columns for Market Place DB Counts, PrecISE DB Counts, and IORS DB counts. In addition to total GTC counts, Core OBSDB, Core Matcher Memory, and Market Place DB counts will be subdivided into DTI, PrecISE, and IORS counts so that we can match across the board. Email alerts will be sent at the following times beginning from EOD after market close:\r\n\r\n1. 6pm â€“ Counts will be executed on:\r\nâ€¢	Core OBSDB â€“ match against MarketPlaceDB on total counts\r\nâ€¢	MarketPlace DB â€“ match against Core OBSDB on total counts\r\nâ€¢	PrecISE DB â€“ match against Core OBSDB and MarketPlace DB on PrecISE only counts\r\nâ€¢	IORS DB  â€“ match against Core OBSDB and MarketPlace DB on IORS only counts \r\n\r\n2. 10pm â€“ Counts will be executed on: (Purpose of this counts is to make sure EOD/Changes did not alter any of the orders)\r\nâ€¢	Core OBSDB â€“ Match against 6pm OBSDB count. \r\no	The report should take into account the number of orders deleted via the CleanOrderbook script and be able to reconcile the differences between 6pm and 10pm based on clean up script count.\r\nâ€¢	MarketPlace DB â€“ Match against 6pm MarketPlaceDB counts.\r\nâ€¢	PrecISE DB â€“ Match against 6pm PrecISE DB counts.\r\nâ€¢	IORS DB â€“ Match against 6pm IORS DB counts.\r\n\r\n3. 2am â€“ Counts will be executed on: (New event that allows us to query Matcher Memory earlier is a prerequisite for this count)\r\nâ€¢	Core Matcher Memory â€“ Match against Core OBSDB 10pm total count\r\no	From this point on, Core OBSDB counts will no longer be accurate due to all non-persistent GT orders being deleted at SOD\r\nâ€¢	IORS MOPSOrderbookInquiry tool? â€“ see follow ups\r\n\r\n4. 3am â€“ Counts will be executed on:\r\nâ€¢	MarketPlace DB â€“ Match against 2am Core Matcher Memory counts\r\n\r\n5. 4am â€“ Counts will be executed on:\r\nâ€¢	PrecISE DB â€“ Match against 3am MarketPlace DB and 2am Core Matcher Memory. \r\n', '2014-01-13 12:22:40', 50),
