('The Fix Simulator service that is used for LOR testing may occasionally stop working if the service is started/stopped too often. The Fix Sim log will not contain an error message but Windows Event Viewer may have the following error:\r\n\r\nService cannot be started. System.ArgumentException: The output char buffer is too small to contain the decoded characters, encoding \\''Unicode (UTF-8)\\'' fallback \\''System.Text.DecoderReplacementFallback\\''.\r\nParameter name: chars\r\n   at System.Text.Encoding.ThrowCharsOverflow(DecoderNLS decoder, Boolean nothingDecoded)\r\n   at System.Text.UTF8Encoding.GetChars(Byte* bytes, Int32 byteCount, Char* chars, Int32 charCount, DecoderNLS baseDecoder)\r\n   at System.Text.DecoderNLS.GetChars(Byte[] bytes, Int32 byteIndex, Int32 byteCount, Char[] chars, Int32 charIndex, Boolean flush)\r\n   at System.Text.DecoderNLS.GetChars(Byte[] bytes, Int32 byteIndex, Int32 byteCount, Char[] chars, Int32 charIndex)\r\n   at System.IO.BinaryReader.InternalReadOneChar()\r\n   at System.IO.BinaryReader.PeekChar()\r\n   at ISE.Library.StreamReceiverAckStatePersistance.StreamReceiverAckStatePersistanceBinaryReaderWriter.ReadRangeBoundary(UInt64& rangeBoundary) in C:\\\\ISE_WD\\\\ISE\\\\library\\\\ISE.StreamReceiverAckStatePersistance\r\n\r\n\r\nIf this is the case, then you\\''ve encountered a known bug. The acceptable work-around is to delete the sequence data files. So, delete the .dat and .log files in the following directories (the directory names may not be identical):\r\n-	D:\\\\ise\\\\EmbeddedFix\r\n-	D:\\\\ise\\\\EmbeddedFix_Gemini\r\n-	D:\\\\ise\\\\log\r\n\r\nNow Fix Simulator should start up again.\r\n', '2014-01-15 13:52:20', 55),
('Matcher MEQ/AON Test --\r\nSetup â€“ occurs for every single test.\r\nTest Setup â€“ \r\nâ€¢	Single ISE Partition with about 20k instrument\r\nâ€¢	All instruments are quoted 57x62 with a quantity of 500\r\nBaseline Setup â€“\r\nâ€¢	7 feeder feeding ABBO in a ramp up\r\nâ€¢	Ramp up is from 25 tps per feeder per second to 775 tps per feeder per second. Rate increases every 10 second.\r\n\r\nTest\r\nTest 1 â€“ Just baseline as mentioned above.\r\n\r\nTest 2 -- There are MEQs on the book not crossed with the IBBO\r\n1.	Enter 40K AON orders â€“ buy only @ $1\r\n2.	ABBO Ramp up with price range is somewhere between 57x62\r\n\r\nTest 3 -- There are MEQs on the book crossed with the IBBO\r\n1.	40k AON â€“ buy @ $62 with quantity of 600 for each order\r\n2.	ABBO baseline Ramp-up\r\n\r\nTest 4 -- There are MEQs on the book crossed with other MEQs\r\n1.	40k AON â€“ buy @ $57 with a quantity of 600 per order\r\n2.	40k AON â€“ sell @ $57 with a quantity of 700 per order\r\n3.	ABBO baseline Ramp-up\r\n\r\nTest 5 -- There are MEQs on the book crossed with numerous IBBO and MEQ levels\r\n1.	Enter additional quotes for all instruments at the following pricing and a fixed quantity of 500 per quote â€“ 57x62| 56x63| 55x64 | 54x65| 53x66\r\n2.	40k AON â€“ buy @ randomly generated price between $57 and $62, with a quantity of 600 per order\r\n3.	40k AON â€“ sell @ randomly generated price between $57 and $62, with a quantity of 700 per order\r\n4.	ABBO baseline Ramp-up\r\n', '2014-01-28 18:04:40', 56),
('https://c9.io\r\n\r\nChange to production branch:\r\n	git checkout production\r\n	\r\nPull down from ISE repo to upstream:\r\n	git fetch upstream\r\n	\r\nsync local puppet folder with production:\r\n	git rebase upstream/production\r\n	\r\nsync github remote origin:\r\n	git push origin production\r\n	\r\nSwitch/Create Branch:\r\n	git branch\r\n	git checkout -b SeriesCount_Update\r\n	\r\nChange to folder you want to edit:\r\n	cd modules/gts/files/ops-scripts/\r\n	\r\nModify/Add Files\r\n\r\nAdd Changes to git:\r\n	git add . # adds everything\r\n	git add <FILE_NAME>\r\n	\r\nCommit Changes:\r\n	git commit\r\n	\r\nPush out branch changes:\r\n	git push -u origin <BRANCH>\r\n\r\nSubmit pull request:\r\n	https://github.com/jwasserzug/puppet\r\n	Click on pull request\r\n	\r\nCheck that commit was fine (on your branch):\r\n	git fetch upstream\r\n	git rebase upstream/production\r\n	rake diffspec\r\n	\r\n\r\n	\r\nIF making a change to commit:\r\n	git checkout -b <BRANCH>\r\n	*make changes*\r\n	git add <change>\r\n	git commit --amend\r\n	git push -f -u origin <BRANCH>', '2014-01-17 14:43:59', 57),
