(' Matcher MEQ/AON PAT Test for 8.1 --\r\nNew field will be added to View DB - MatcherGenMEParameters view with the name AwayMktFadeTriggersMEQ.\r\n\r\n If this value is set to false, the matcher should behave as it does today (i.e. ABBO price change should not trigger a match attempt on AON/MEQ orders).  If the value is set to true, the behavior will follow new logic.\r\n\r\nWe should run all 5 tests against 8.0 (as a baseline) and then all 5 tests against 8.1 with the new functionality turned off, and then against 8.1 with the new functionality turned on, to ensure we havenâ€™t caused any significant problems.', '2014-01-28 18:06:39', 70),
('Brainstorm on TAP Controller requirements -- SIR 259064\r\n\r\n1. Web FE to start test run.\r\n2. Web FE to display test run status (queuing,running and percentage,completed), start/stop time stamp and test result location.(a link to the robot report)\r\n3.  Able to group test cases into test batches.\r\n4. Able to identify test requirements and server resources. Thus matching the right environment with the right test.\r\n5. Able to simultaneously kick off multiple tests in different env.\r\n6. Able to remotely kick off robot tests. (We can run multiple tests simultaneously on a single robot master server instance)\r\n7. Able to queue up tests that\\''s for the same env.\r\n8. Able to kill an ongoing test.\r\n9. Able to keep a history of executed tests. (retention tbd)\r\n10. Able to accept test request from external automated sources/tools. (i.e. puppet might turn over a new build, and submit a test request for testing the new version) (Make it restful, with JSON object?)\r\n11. Able to output back test run status to external sources (queuing, running, completed).\r\n12. Able to schedule or work with a scheduler to run test during prescheduled times.\r\n13. Able to manually force tests to run on a particular env/svr.\r\n14. User permission.\r\n15. For ongoing or queued tests, show test requester, just in case we need to kill someone\\''s test.\r\n16. Email/Text notification of events. (i.e. test results)\r\n17. Accept test request via email.\r\n18. Able to specify maximum test run time. If exceeded, then test run gets killed.\r\n19. Allow priorities to be placed on tests, instead of first come first serve.\r\n20. Allow admin to manually modify test queue.\r\n21. Allow requester to specify how many time a test should run.\r\n22. Have groups of \\"always-test\\" test cases. If any env is idle for 30 min, then these tests get kicked off. Any time a test request comes in, these tests get killed to give way to the new test request.\r\n23. Allow users to have shortcuts to frequently tested test cases.\r\n24. Allow notes on test cases.\r\n25. Allow requester to add people to test result recipient list.\r\n26. Able to detect redundancies in test cases. For example, if a test is running, and a new test request comes in for the same test, then new requester will get prompt that the test is already running, and will have the option of simply adding himself/herself to result recipient.\r\n27. Livestream of Robot Remote Server screen output to web page.\r\n28. Livestream of Robot Master Server screen output to web page.\r\n29. Graphing capability to present various stats.\r\n30. Sound, points, and trivia.', '2014-01-29 18:22:01', 71),
('Curtailment Events are market maker protection messages (in the form of a PQB, Private Quote Broadcast) sent from Matcher. \r\nThis messages/event is an indication that the traded quantity, of a particular product, for a particular market maker, has exceeded the tolerable limit that\\''s set by the market maker.\r\nThis message is then used by MWSB to pull all of MM\\''s quotes from all products.\r\nIn other words, curtailment is by product, by BU.\r\n\r\nMarket Maker sets the curtailment quantity threshold by send in using MMParameterDefinitionRequest. This value is then retained in obsdb\\''s marketmakerparameters table.\r\n\r\nFYI -- the lowest quantity that can be set via that message is 10. All other thresholds like percentage, Delta, Vega have minimum value of 100.\r\n', '2014-01-29 13:55:02', 72),
('To find the role of a market maker for a specific product, go to viewdb.MatcherMarketMakerRoles table, and select by productid.\r\n\r\n1 -- PMM\r\n2 -- backup PMM\r\n3 -- CMM', '2014-01-29 13:56:28', 73),
('When opening Sikuli, if you get the following error:\r\n\r\n[error] Location: outside any screen (1276, -4) - subsequent actions might not work as expected\r\n\r\nThen do the following:\r\n1. Open Windows Registry Editor (regedit from command prompt)\r\n2. Go to: HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\\\Software\\\\JavaSoft\\\\Prefs\\\\org\\\\sikuli\r\n3. Delete all folders under the sikuli folder (I deleted the basics folder)\r\n4. Run Sikuli again. That error should not happen. Restart PC if it persists.\r\n\r\nhttps://bugs.launchpad.net/sikuli/+bug/1226012', '2014-01-29 14:33:12', 74),
